    "privileged_info_summary": "The task requires generating a 1D spatial cross-section of precipitation for January at 15\u00b0S over South America using real NCEP long-term mean data (prate.sfc.mon.ltm.nc downloaded from NOAA). Direct analysis of the netCDF data reveals that the closest grid latitude to 15\u00b0S is -14.2855\u00b0. At this latitude, the windward precipitation peak occurs at longitude 290.62\u00b0E (69.38\u00b0W) with a precipitation rate of ~0.0001217 kg/m\u00b2/s, while the leeward desert minimum occurs west of the Andes at longitude 279.38\u00b0E (80.62\u00b0W) with a rate of ~2.078e-07 kg/m\u00b2/s. Expected outputs are andean_cross_section.png and rain_shadow_report.txt saved to /home/ga/Documents/OrographicStudy/.",
